  "prompt": "Why does Dushka Zapat refer to her boyfriend as 'Boyfriend' and not 'My Boyfriend' ?",
  "response": "Dushka Zapata, known for her unique writing style and thoughtful reflections, often refers to her boyfriend simply as 'Boyfriend' rather than 'my boyfriend' to provide a more universal and relatable context to her readers. By doing so, she removes any possessive connotation, allowing her audience to see 'Boyfriend' as a character or concept that can easily be imagined in their own experiences. This approach can make her writing feel more accessible and inclusive, as it invites readers to connect with the feelings and scenarios she describes without the specificity that might distance them if she used possessive terms.",
